Captain Cooper Elementary Dashboard Summary

Report Purpose

This report is created to assist Captain Cooper Elementary in reflecting on the student groups whose indicators led to Differentiated Assistance for Carmel Unified.

Qualifying Groups

Differentiated Assistance is determined by the California Dashboard. Colors reflect the latest available status from 2022. For all graphs, the darker the color the lower the status.

The graphic below shows the color for each student group for each indicator from the California 2022 Dashboard.

California Dashboard 2022

The graph below displays which student groups qualified Carmel Unified to be eligible for Differentiated Assistance. Moreover, for each student group it shows which Priority Areas and associated indicators met qualification criteria.

As a reminder, COEs must offer differentiated assistance to a school district if any student group meets the criteria for two or more LCFF priorities according to California Education Code Section 52071(c). Californiaâs System of Support

For Captain Cooper Elementary, the below graph shows how at the school level their student groups did at the school level which contributed to Carmel Unified as an LEA overall.

Note this graph also includes student groups with 11 to 29 students in them to provide a fuller picture even if those groups are not used for state accountability calculations such as CSI/ATSI.

CSI/ATSI Designations

Under ESSA, schools can be identified for Comprehensive Support and Improvement (CSI) or Additional Targeted Support and Improvement (ATSI). CSI is based on a schoolâs overall or All Students indicators, whereas ATSI is based on each student groupâs indicators. For more information please see: CDE School Support. It is important to note that calculations are only based on student groups with 30 or more students, which means not all the indicators on the previous graph will be used.

This school is eligible for CSI.

There are no student groups at this school that are eligible for ATSI.

Status Needed to Avoid Red in 2023

This section estimates the limits for indicators to receive an orange or higher color next year on the 2023 Dashboard. The thresholds below are based on the 5x5 grids last approved by the State Board of Education and the number of students in the 2022 calculation. State policies may change and the student counts may shift. Only student groups in DA and their qualifying indicators for Carmel Unified are included below and only if they are in the lowest status for Captain Cooper Elementary. The thresholds represent the numbers for Captain Cooper Elementary.
